ded by water in the Caribbean, so it's important for us to develop the Beach Games and make it a signature Special Olympic event for the Caribbean,\\\" said Special Olympics Caribbean Initiative Executive Director Lorna Bell.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1167, \"end\": 1183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.3291124201025467e-12, \"text\": \"Special Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean_Initiative\", \"score\": 0.9999999998890416, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caribbean Initiative\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean_Initiative\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean_Initiative\"}, {\"begin\": 1224, \"end\": 1229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lorna_Luft\", \"score\": 0.9999996270679061, \"rank\": 3.1273419177804924e-07, \"text\": \"Lorna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lorna_Luft\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lorna_Luft\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1025}, {\"ngram\": \"the Caribbean\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1042}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1068}, {\"ngram\": \"the Beach Games\", \"from\": 1080, \"to\": 1095}, {\"ngram\": \"Special Olympic event\", \"from\": 1120, \"to\": 1141}, {\"ngram\": \"the Caribbean\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1159}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We believe that sports can play a major role in promoting inclusion, understanding, and respect, and we hope that these Games will demonstrate our commitment and capacity to host events in our region that would inspire more people to support Special Olympics athletes,\\\" she explained.\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1480, \"end\": 1496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.3291124201025467e-12, \"text\": \"Special Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1260}, {\"ngram\": \"a major role\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1282}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1305}, {\"ngram\": \"understanding\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1320}, {\"ngram\": \"respect\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1333}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1363}, {\"ngram\": \"our commitment\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1395}, {\"ngram\": \"capacity\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1408}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1423}, {\"ngram\": \"our region\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1437}, {\"ngram\": \"more people\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1468}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Partnering with regional governments, particularly as it relates to policymaking aimed at improving the lives of people with intellectual disabilities, is also a crucial component.\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1704, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"regional governments\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1560}, {\"ngram\": \"the lives\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1633}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1637, \"to\": 1643}, {\"ngram\": \"intellectual disabilities\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1674}, {\"ngram\": \"a crucial component\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1703}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jamaica, through its Ministry of Sport, is the only Caribbean country to have signed the Special Olympics global leadership coalition for inclusion, which ratifies agreements between national programmes and their governments.\", \"from\": 1706, \"to\": 1931, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1706, \"end\": 1713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999579365478247, \"rank\": 4.1280868026854054e-05, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its Ministry\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1735}, {\"ngram\": \"Sport\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1744}, {\"ngram\": \"the only Caribbean country\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1775}, {\"ngram\": \"the Special Olympics global leadership coalition\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1853}, {\"ngram\": \"agreements\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1880}, {\"ngram\": \"national programmes\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 1908}, {\"ngram\": \"their governments\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1930}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bell said she is thrilled that Trinidad and Tobago is set to sign the coalition during the Beach Games.\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 2036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1964, \"end\": 1972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinidad_and_Tobago\", \"score\": 0.9993791263603915, \"rank\": 0.0006139186908766142, \"text\": \"Trinidad\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinidad_and_Tobago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinidad_and_Tobago\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bell\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1937}, {\"ngram\": \"Tobago\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 1983}, {\"ngram\": \"the coalition\", \"from\": 1999, \"to\": 2012}, {\"ngram\": \"the Beach Games\", \"from\": 2020, \"to\": 2035}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I'd like to congratulate Trinidad and Tobago for being ready to join the coalition.\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2064, \"end\": 2072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinidad_and_Tobago\", \"score\": 0.9993791263603915, \"rank\": 0.0006139186908766142, \"text\": \"Trinidad\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinidad_and_Toba